.\" Man page for one-click
.TH ONE-CLICK 8 "@DATE@" "One-Click v@VERSION@" "System Administration"

.SH NAME
one-click \- modular server management, recovery, backup, and migration toolkit

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B one-click
.RI [ command ]

.B one-click help

.B one-click cron

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B one-click
is a modular server management and disaster recovery toolkit designed for predictable,
repeatable, and auditable Linux system administration.

It provides tools for operating system reinstallation, backup, migration, boot recovery,
network repair, automation, and system inspection.

The toolkit is designed for use on VPS, dedicated servers, and bare-metal systems.
Operations may be interactive or automated.

Long-running operations are automatically executed within a
.BR tmux (1)
session to prevent interruption from SSH disconnects.

Commands are explicit and user-initiated. Destructive operations require confirmation.

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B reinstall
Perform a destructive operating system reinstallation over the network.

.TP
.B backup
Create incremental or compressed backups locally or remotely.

.TP
.B boot-recovery
Create or restore boot and root partition snapshots.

.TP
.B repair
Repair or restore network configurations.

.TP
.B migrate
Migrate entire systems using block-level or file-level methods.

.TP
.B sys-info
Display live system statistics.

.TP
.B cron
Configure scheduled automation tasks.

.TP
.B uninstall
Remove one-click and all associated files.

.TP
.B help
Display the interactive help menu.

.SH OPTIONS
Currently,
.B one-click
uses subcommands instead of traditional command-line options.

Future versions may introduce additional flags.

